description:
&lt;p&gt;NHS Blood and Transplant (NHSBT) Histocompatibility and Immunogenetics (H&amp;I) laboratories provide a range of diagnostic and reference services to meet the needs of patients and those who treat them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The H&amp;I department in Colindale provides testing and support services for transplantation, transfusion and immunogenetic diagnostic testing and performs typing of platelet donors, bone marrow volunteers and cord blood donors for the NHSBT panels using Next Generation Sequencing technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working at the Colindale laboratory, you will provide vital support to qualified scientific staff in a role which includes sample reception, DNA extraction and general laboratory support duties. The role of the HHTO also includes entering donor and patient information into the laboratory database and the generation of computerised worksheets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work 37.5 hours per week, 08:00-16:30 Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a dynamic and friendly working environment where teamwork is highly valued. Personal development is also considered a priority and our extensive training and development opportunities are open to all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries please contact Aliyye Karasu at Aliyye.karasu@nhsbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy will close at midnight 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will take place on 26th November&lt;/p&gt;
